# Component reuse — single source of truth

**Binding (Andrew 2026-06-11):** post-redesign, **no duplicate components** unless absolutely necessary (document why). Every complex component **composes** shared lower-level components/primitives — not re-implemented per page. Styling and behavior are **single-source**: fix a shared component once; every consumer updates. No per-page hardcoded colors/spacing.

## Rules

1. **No duplication** — before adding a component, check [`docs/V1-COMPONENT-LIBRARY.md`](../../docs/V1-COMPONENT-LIBRARY.md) §1 inventory. Extend canonicals; do not fork.
2. **Compose, don't copy** — complex UIs = shared primitives (`ui/*`, §1A patterns, inventory canonicals), not inline duplicate JSX.
3. **Tokens + shared components only** — no hardcoded color/style literals; pairs with §2.11 theme-agnostic gate.
4. **Done = grep-clean** — no duplicated structure or one-off styling that should live in a shared component.

